              <img src="images/doublecrux.png" class="image-in-desc"/>
              <p>
                <a href="http://double-crux.appspot.com/">Double Crux</a> was a first attempt at making an online format for the Double Crux <a href="http://rationality.org/resources/updates/2016/double-crux">conversational technique</a>.
              </p>
              <p>
                It’s designed to be a forum that hosts split-screen discussions for two people. Each discussion’s sub-points (“cruxes”) can be recursed upon to form new split-screen discussions. The code can be found on Github <a href="https://github.com/Vanzcoder/finalproject">here</a>.
              </p>
